🗒️ UNIDEV Notes Application – Project Report
1. 📌 Project Description
This project aims to develop a simple yet functional mobile application that allows users to easily create, edit, and categorize text-based notes.

2. ✅ Application Requirements
Functional Requirements:

Add new notes

Edit existing notes

Delete notes

Assign categories (tags) to notes

(Optional) Search notes by content or category

Technical Requirements:

Platforms: iOS and Android

Development Environment: Flutter (Dart)

Single codebase for both platforms

Rapid prototyping capabilities

Rich UI components

Data Storage:

Local storage via Hive or SharedPreferences

(Optionally) Cloud synchronization using Firebase

3. 🎨 User Interface (UI) Design
Screens:

Home Screen (Note List)

Displays all saved notes

Category tag shown alongside each note

A “+” button to add new notes

Long press options: “Edit” and “Delete”

Add/Edit Note Screen

Fields for title, note content, and category selector

Save button

Category Management (Optional)

Users can define custom categories/tags

Design Principles:

Material Design (Android-friendly)

Simple, clean, and minimal UI

High contrast and large font sizes for readability

4. 🔧 Application Development Process
Tools Used:

Flutter SDK

Dart Programming Language

Visual Studio Code / Android Studio

Figma (for UI prototyping)

Development Steps:

Flutter project initialized

Note model defined (title, content, category, date)

Hive local database integrated

Home screen and edit screen implemented

Tagging system and filtering logic added

Basic functional tests conducted

Application tested on Android Emulator and iOS Simulator

